\begin{tcbProblem}[label={problem:0006:question:Eng}]
	The sum of the squares of the first ten natural numbers is,
	\begin{equation*}
		{1}^{2} \mathplus {2}^{2} \mathplus \unicodecdots \mathplus {10}^{2} \equal 385
	\end{equation*}
	The square of the sum of the first ten natural numbers is,
	\begin{equation*}
		{\lparen 1 \mathplus 2 \mathplus \unicodecdots \mathplus 10 \rparen}^{2} \equal {55}^{2} \equal 3025	
	\end{equation*}
	Hence the difference between the sum of the squares of the first ten natural numbers and the square of the sum is \( 3025 \minus 385 \equal 2640 \).

	Find the difference between the sum of the squares of the first one hundred natural numbers and the square of the sum.
	\par%
	\hrefOriginalPage{6}%
	\tcbline%
	最初の10個の自然数について，その二乗の和は，
	\begin{equation*}
		{1}^{2} \mathplus {2}^{2} \mathplus \unicodecdots \mathplus {10}^{2} \equal 385
	\end{equation*}
	最初の10個の自然数について，その和の二乗は，
	\begin{equation*}
		{\lparen 1 \mathplus 2 \mathplus \unicodecdots \mathplus 10 \rparen}^{2} \equal {55}^{2} \equal 3025	
	\end{equation*}
	これらの数の差は\( 3025 \minus 385 \equal 2640 \)となる．
	同様にして，最初の100個の自然数について二乗の和と和の二乗の差を求めよ．
	\par%
